about.summary: Provides very fast read and write access to images stored in the NIfTI-1 and ANALYZE-7.5 formats, with seamless synchronisation between compiled C and interpreted R code. Also provides a C/C++ API that can be used by other packages. Not to be confused with 'RNiftyReg', which performs image registration.

name: r-rnifti
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rnifti
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/RNifti_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/RNifti/RNifti_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f6e2cb3e45d7bf6db3aeca820928fa8d21729dc8c83a4635e0286035ae8d16fd

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('RNifti')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('RNifti')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/jonclayden/RNifti
  license: GPL-2
  summary: Provides very fast read and write access to images stored in the NIfTI-1 and ANALYZE-7.5
    formats, with seamless synchronisation between compiled C and interpreted R code.
    Also provides a C/C++ API that can be used by other packages. Not to be confused
    with 'RNiftyReg', which performs image registration.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
